The paper focuses on game theory and multiagent systems, which are core topics in computer science. The paper specifically deals with the design of agents' utility functions for resource allocation problems, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and multiagent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the optimization of the price of anarchy, which is a topic in both machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with distributed systems, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
